19 July 2012The Inter-Ministerial Committee on the Gauteng Freeway Improvement Project (GFIP), which is chaired by Deputy President Kgalema Motlanthe, will meet with COSATU as part of stakeholder consultations on the GFIP. Media are invited to a photo-opportunity scheduled to take place just before the start of the meeting. The meeting details are:Date: Friday, 20 July 2012 Time: 9h30-11h00 (Photographers should arrive at 9h15) Venue: Cosatu House, 110 Jorissen Street, JohannesburgAt the end of the meeting, a statement on the outcomes of the meeting will be issued to all media Media wishing to attend must please RSVP: Pheliswa Sebati Cell: 082 413 4609 E-mail: Pheliswa@gcis.gov.za or Nthabiseng Rantao Cell: 082 570 5503 E-mail:Nthabiseng@po.gov.za Enquiries: Thabo Masebe Cell: 082 410 8087Issued by Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)